1. Add CSS comments in your CSS block.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Web Page</title>
    <style>
        
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4; 
            text-align: center;
        }

        
        header {
            background-color: #007bff; 
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        
        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #333;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #28a745; 
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
        }


        button:hover {
            background-color: #218838; 
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
        <p>This is a simple web page with HTML and CSS.</p>
        <button>Click Me</button>
    </section>
</body>
</html>

2. Create a page with different background-colour of a page and set an image as the background-image of a page (image should not scroll with the rest of the page and specify the size of a background image)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Background Image Page</title>
    <style>
        
        body {
            background-color: #f0f0f0; 
            background-image: url('background.jpg'); 
            background-size: cover; 
            background-attachment: fixed; 
            background-position: center; 
            background-repeat: no-repeat; 
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            height: 100vh;
        }

        
        .content {
            text-align: center;
            color: white;
            padding: 50px;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); 
            margin: 100px auto;
            width: 50%;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="content">
        <h1>Welcome to My Page</h1>
        <p>This page has a fixed background image and a different background color.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

3. Create a different page with the width, style and color of the 4 border-style(set different borders on each side with different patterns).
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Border Styles Page</title>
    <style>
        
        .border-box {
            width: 300px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 18px;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            
            
            border-top: 5px solid red; 
            border-right: 5px dashed blue;
            border-bottom: 5px dotted green;
            border-left: 5px double black; 
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="border-box">
        <p>This box has different border styles on each side.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

4. Develop a page and set the height:(in pixels and %) and width:(in pixels and %) on elements.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Height and Width Example</title>
    <style>
       
        .container {
            width: 80%;
            height: 400px; 
            background-color: lightblue;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 20px;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        
        .box {
            width: 50%; 
            height: 50%; 
            background-color: coral;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="box">
            Responsive Box
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

5. Develop a page with different font-styles, font-size, font-family, colors and text-align.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Text Styling Example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
            color: darkblue;
            text-align: center;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            font-family: 'Verdana', sans-serif;
            color: darkred;
            text-align: justify;
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .highlight {
            font-size: 22px;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            color: green;
            text-align: left;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Styled Page</h1>
    <p>This paragraph has different font styles, font size, font family, and text alignment.</p>
    <p class="highlight">This is a highlighted text with bold, different font, and left-aligned.</p>
</body>
</html>
